15#ifndef DNS_DBTABLE_H
16#define DNS_DBTABLE_H 1
17
18/*****
19 ***** Module Info
20 *****/
21
22/*! \file dns/dbtable.h
23 * \brief
24 * DNS DB Tables
25 *
26 * XXX TBS XXX
27 *
28 * MP:
29 *\li The module ensures appropriate synchronization of data structures it
30 * creates and manipulates.
31 *
32 * Reliability:
33 *\li No anticipated impact.
34 *
35 * Resources:
36 *\li None.
37 *
38 * Security:
39 *\li No anticipated impact.
40 *
41 * Standards:
42 *\li None.
43 */
44
45#include <isc/lang.h>
46
47#include <dns/types.h>
48
49#define DNS_DBTABLEFIND_NOEXACT 0x01
50
51ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
52
53isc_result_t
54dns_dbtable_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_rdataclass_t rdclass,
55 dns_dbtable_t **dbtablep);
56/*%<
57 * Make a new dbtable of class 'rdclass'
58 *
59 * Requires:
60 *\li mctx != NULL
61 * \li dbtablep != NULL && *dptablep == NULL
62 *\li 'rdclass' is a valid class
63 *
64 * Returns:
65 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS
66 *\li #ISC_R_NOMEMORY
67 *\li #ISC_R_UNEXPECTED
68 */
69
70void
71dns_dbtable_attach(dns_dbtable_t *source, dns_dbtable_t **targetp);
72/*%<
73 * Attach '*targetp' to 'source'.
74 *
75 * Requires:
76 *
77 *\li 'source' is a valid dbtable.
78 *
79 *\li 'targetp' points to a NULL dns_dbtable_t *.
80 *
81 * Ensures:
82 *
83 *\li *targetp is attached to source.
84 */
85
86void
87dns_dbtable_detach(dns_dbtable_t **dbtablep);
88/*%<
89 * Detach *dbtablep from its dbtable.
90 *
91 * Requires:
92 *
93 *\li '*dbtablep' points to a valid dbtable.
94 *
95 * Ensures:
96 *
97 *\li *dbtablep is NULL.
98 *
99 *\li If '*dbtablep' is the last reference to the dbtable,
100 * all resources used by the dbtable will be freed
101 */
102
103isc_result_t
104dns_dbtable_add(dns_dbtable_t *dbtable, dns_db_t *db);
105/*%<
106 * Add 'db' to 'dbtable'.
107 *
108 * Requires:
109 *\li 'dbtable' is a valid dbtable.
110 *
111 *\li 'db' is a valid database with the same class as 'dbtable'
112 */
113
114void
115dns_dbtable_remove(dns_dbtable_t *dbtable, dns_db_t *db);
116/*%<
117 * Remove 'db' from 'dbtable'.
118 *
119 * Requires:
120 *\li 'db' was previously added to 'dbtable'.
121 */
122
123void
124dns_dbtable_adddefault(dns_dbtable_t *dbtable, dns_db_t *db);
125/*%<
126 * Use 'db' as the result of a dns_dbtable_find() if no better match is
127 * available.
128 */
129
130void
131dns_dbtable_getdefault(dns_dbtable_t *dbtable, dns_db_t **db);
132/*%<
133 * Get the 'db' used as the result of a dns_dbtable_find()
134 * if no better match is available.
135 */
136
137void
138dns_dbtable_removedefault(dns_dbtable_t *dbtable);
139/*%<
140 * Remove the default db from 'dbtable'.
141 */
142
143isc_result_t
144dns_dbtable_find(dns_dbtable_t *dbtable, const dns_name_t *name,
145 unsigned int options, dns_db_t **dbp);
146/*%<
147 * Find the deepest match to 'name' in the dbtable, and return it
148 *
149 * Notes:
150 *\li If the DNS_DBTABLEFIND_NOEXACT option is set, the best partial
151 * match (if any) to 'name' will be returned.
152 *
153 * Returns:
154 * \li #ISC_R_SUCCESS on success
155 *\li something else: no default and match
156 */
157
158ISC_LANG_ENDDECLS
159
160#endif /* DNS_DBTABLE_H */
161
